================================================================================
          THE CLANKER ARCHITECTURAL WISDOM & DESIGN PHILOSOPHY
================================================================================

This document synthesizes the architectural direction, core compilation rules, 
and design patterns developed for clank-compiler.py. It represents the structural 
principles to guide future updates, refactoring, and AI-assisted extensions.

---

[1] SYSTEM PATH SEGREGATION
- repo_dir (The Repository Directory):
  The active working directory where the developer compiles targets. It is 
  resolved dynamically at runtime from where the script is executed.
- script_dir (The Script Directory):
  The static location where the compiler script and standard pipeline source files 
  reside. This directory is strictly isolated from repo_dir to prevent assets 
  from polluting the active codebase.

---

[2] THE PHILOSOPHY OF "SEPARATING HIGH AND LOW"
Utility scripts degrade when logical mechanics (the "how") get tangled with 
declarative intents (the "what"). For maximum ease of maintenance, the file 
should be divided into clearly visible zones:

- High-Level Declarative Zone (Top of File):
  Contains path lookup strategies, custom syntax symbols, and prompt compilation 
  pipelines (the letter-to-fragment routing tables). Changing the user interface, 
  updating fallbacks, or adding new tool modes should require only editing a 
  high-level configuration dictionary.
  
- Low-Level Plumbing Zone (Bottom of File):
  Contains OS-level terminal wrappers, keyboard listeners, clipboard writers, and 
  recursive template expansion functions. Once written, these mechanics should 
  remain static and completely decoupled from specific project details.

---

[3] THE PARSING GRAMMAR & WHITESPACE ALIGNMENT
The compilation engine operates on a silent, raw, recursive lookup scheme. To 
ensure the generated LLM prompts remain highly readable and syntactically clean, 
the compiler adheres to strict formatting standards:

- Subsequent-Line Placeholder Structure:
  Avoid placing consecutive tags on a single line. If tags are placed on the 
  same line, the recursive raw string replacement will mash compiled codeblocks 
  together horizontally. Place placeholders on separate, vertical lines.
  
- Indentation Mirroring:
  Since the compiler does a literal string replace without adjusting indents, 
  child fragments must pre-indent their content. This ensures they align with the 
  parent block once spliced into the master game-runtime layout.

- Human vs. Machine Segregation:
  Files are split into a human-facing comment block (top) and an LLM-facing 
  payload block (bottom) separated by the marker line: "--- START PROMPT ---".
  The compiler strips away the human documentation during compilation, sending 
  only dense XML-style prompt contexts to the clipboard.

---

[4] KEY CODES & SHELL OPTIMIZATIONS
- Raw TTY Listening:
  Single-character keystroke reads provide immediate menu action, avoiding 
  sluggish terminal inputs.
- OSC 52 Copy Sequence:
  Using standard base64 and terminal control escape sequences allows copy-to-clipboard 
  functionality to work natively, even across SSH tunnels and terminal multiplexers 
  without relying on OS dependencies.
- Loop Prevention:
  Explicit stack-tracking of visited paths prevents include cycles when resolving 
  recursive placeholders.
================================================================================
